The reading assignments listed below are what you should read before coming to
class. The class lectures assume this reading has been done, and while you may
not completely understand the material you will have a familiarity with the
concepts and transactions we will be covering each day. Additional short
readings (e.g., recent business press articles) will be distributed in class.
Readings that refer to "Pratt" can be found in the course textbook, J. Pratt,
Financial Accounting in an Economic Context, 5th ed., John Wiley &amp; Sons,
Inc. Other readings are from the Intel 2002 Annual Report, which is available
for download from the Web_site.Â "CP" stands for the Case Pack of readings that
students purchase.
